1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Nobody tells you this when you first start dirt biking.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,500
The hard part is not about learning how to ride,

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,000
it's actually finding somebody who gets it.

4
00:00:08,730 --> 00:00:12,730
My first real ride was brutal.

5
00:00:12,730 --> 00:00:16,730
100 degrees out, sweating through everything,

6
00:00:16,730 --> 00:00:20,330
legs shaking, hands tired — I could barely stay on the bike.

7
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:24,330
But you know what the crazy thing is? I couldn't stop thinking about it.

8
00:00:24,330 --> 00:00:28,330
That's when I realized dirt biking is addictive.

9
00:00:28,330 --> 00:00:31,830
And it gets even better when you have somebody to share it with.

10
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:35,630
But most of what I found online felt scattered, outdated,

11
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:39,300
or just not the way I wanted it to be built.

12
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:44,580
So as a software engineer, I set out to do the one thing I know how — build DirtBikeX

13
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:50,740
myself. The kind of place I wish existed. No bloat. You don't have to post

14
00:00:50,740 --> 00:00:56,100
the same thing twice. 21 languages. All the good stuff.

15
00:00:56,100 --> 00:01:01,300
Most importantly, a real chance for us to be seen by fellow riders. So if you've been looking

16
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:07,540
for dirt bike people like me, go check out the invite code in the description. My name is Rubio,

17
00:01:07,540 --> 00:01:09,670
and I'll be waiting for you there!
